easychem
------------------------------------------
EasyChem is a program designed to draw chemical molecules, 
written under Linux and using Gtk+ 2.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  gdk-pixbuf2-2.10.12-1
  glib2-2.12.12-1
  gtk2-x11-2.10.12-1
  libintl8-0.15-1
  pango-1.16.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.2.11-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gettext-devel-0.15-1
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.21-1

Canonical website:
  http://easychem.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/easychem/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack easychem-0.6-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./easychem-0.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/easychem-0.6-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/easychem-0.6-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/easychem.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/easychem-0.6.README
  /usr/share/doc/easychem-0.6/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/easychem-0.6/TODO
  /usr/share/locale/fr/LC_MESSAGES/easychem.mo

------------------

Port Notes:

